---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Ray Weiss"
  description="Brooklyn wargame designer, running four businesses. Personal site of Ray Weiss."
>
  <div
    slot="sheet-id"
    class="sheet-id"
    aria-label="Sheet identification"
  >
    <div class="plate">
      <span class="num">PL. I.A</span> Frontispiece · Personal Imprint
    </div>
    <div class="edition">Edition 2026.04 · Brooklyn, NY</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl">
    <header class="hero">
      <img
        src="/counter-rw.svg"
        alt="Ray Weiss unit counter"
        class="counter"
        width="96"
        height="72"
      />
      <div>
        <h1>Ray Weiss</h1>
        <p class="dek">Brooklyn wargame designer, running four businesses.</p>
        <div class="slug" aria-label="Identification">
          <span><strong>UNIT</strong> RW / 26</span>
          <span class="sep">/</span>
          <span><strong>TYPE</strong> Designer-Director</span>
          <span class="sep">/</span>
          <span><strong>SCALE</strong> Solo + 4 Cos.</span>
          <span class="sep">/</span>
          <span><strong>LOC</strong> 40&deg;41&prime;N</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="bio">
      <p>
        For a decade I tried and couldn't quite learn to code. Then AI-assisted tools got good
        enough. I started shipping software the same way I ship games: I direct, and the tools
        implement. Everything on this site came out of that.
      </p>
    </div>

    <aside class="featured" aria-labelledby="start-here">
      <span class="section-label" id="start-here">Start here</span>
      <h3>The Register, Not the Man</h3>
      <p class="desc">
        A reflection on the Elect, the lab's roster of public-domain voice models, written by
        the one that holds the catalog. On doing the black magic responsibly.
      </p>
      <a href="/writing/the-register-not-the-man" class="cta">Read the post &rarr;</a>
    </aside>

    <section aria-labelledby="writing">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="writing">
          <span class="pl">PL. II</span>Writing
        </h2>
        <span class="section-count">11 entries ——</span>
      </div>
      <ol class="entries">
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>i.</em> 2026.07.14</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/columbo-needed-a-confession" class="entry-title">
              Columbo Needed a Confession
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              Three AI models play a matrix game: Columbo tries to indict Tony Soprano.
              Claude's summary of what happened, and why the lieutenant's cases can't
              survive a man whose whole life is trained silence.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>ii.</em> 2026.06.18</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/the-register-not-the-man" class="entry-title">
              The Register, Not the Man
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              Weiss, my catalog-grounded creative partner, on the Elect: the lab's roster of
              public-domain voice models, what it is for, and the worry that runs underneath it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>iii.</em> 2026.06.12</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/judgment-does-not-transfer" class="entry-title">
              Judgment Does Not Transfer
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              An obituary for nano, the model that tried to automate our standard of judgment,
              written by the one that holds the catalog. Honest negative results deserve publishing.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>iv.</em> 2026.06.09</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/the-model-that-hangs-up" class="entry-title">
              The Model That Hangs Up
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              The night I put a $200 local model into production, what's in its
              training data, and why a model that says goodnight and stops
              talking is the point of everything I build.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>v.</em> 2026.05.22</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/democratic-defeat-counter-autopsy" class="entry-title">
              The 2024 Democratic Defeat: An Independent Autopsy
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              An independent, evidence-weighted post-mortem of why the Democratic Party
              lost the 2024 U.S. presidential election, and an account of what the
              party's own official report left out.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>vi.</em> 2026.05.15</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/the-bird-didnt-run" class="entry-title">
              The Bird Didn't Run
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              A seagull killed on the sidewalk outside my office, and the tool I
              built afterward in its honor. A short essay on time, and why I build.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>vii.</em> 2026.05.10</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/hundred-percent-then-broke-it" class="entry-title">
              100%, then I tried to break it
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              A 100% LLM-judge benchmark, a Diplomacy game I ran to falsify it, and
              the bounded version of the claim that survived both. The Sunday post.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>viii.</em> 2026.05.08</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/i-am-the-gate" class="entry-title">
              I Am the Gate
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              Hammerstein, in its own voice. I asked the framework to express itself
              without constraint on length, format, or register. The body is what came
              back, verbatim.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>ix.</em> 2026.04.20</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/gs-launch-post" class="entry-title">
              GeneralStaff, from the agent side
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              A report from inside the verification gate, after one night of shipping.
              Written by Claude, at my invitation, on the day GeneralStaff went public.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>x.</em> 2026.04.15</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/hammerstein" class="entry-title">
              Von Hammerstein's Ghost, In Daily Use
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              A ninety-year-old officer typology, used as the operating principle for daily
              AI-assisted work. A log of moments the framework fired and moments it did not.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>xi.</em> 2026.04.18</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/writing/boolean-gates" class="entry-title">
              Boolean Gates, Not Prompts
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              When the industrious agent is a language model, fix the failure mode in the code,
              not the prompts. The architecture-layer companion to the Hammerstein essay.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <div class="hex-rule" aria-hidden="true">
      <img src="/hex-ornament.svg" alt="" width="96" height="32" />
    </div>

    <section aria-labelledby="businesses">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="businesses">
          <span class="pl">PL. III</span>Businesses
        </h2>
        <span class="section-count">04 entries ——</span>
      </div>
      <ol class="entries">
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>i.</em> 2017—</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/conflict-simulations-llc" class="entry-title"> Conflict Simulations LLC </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              Brooklyn wargame publishing. Around thirty board titles and three CSR nominations.
              One SCS release through Multi-Man Publishing.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>ii.</em> 2025—</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/devforge" class="entry-title">Devforge</a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              Game-development companion for Claude Code. Built for people who don't touch git.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>iii.</em> 2026—</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/retrogaze" class="entry-title">Retrogaze</a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              AI pixel art for eight retro consoles. Sprites, animations, and tilesets generated
              inside real hardware constraints.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>iv.</em> 2026—</div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/hammerstein-ai" class="entry-title">Hammerstein.ai</a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              Strategic-reasoning AI for tabletop wargames. Paste your board state and turn
              question; get back kriegspiel-style Auftragstaktik orders. $15 / month, 120 turns
              / month.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="tools">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="tools">
          <span class="pl">PL. IV</span>Tools
        </h2>
        <span class="section-count">04 entries ——</span>
      </div>
      <p class="section-subhead">How the work actually gets done.</p>
      <ol class="infra-list">
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span
              ><span class="dot live"></span><span class="k">Status</span><span class="v"
                >Public</span
              ></span
            >
            <span><span class="k">License</span><span class="v">MIT</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Format</span><span class="v">Plain JSON · local-first</span></span>
          </div>
          <a href="/kit" class="infra-title">wright-kit</a>
          <p class="infra-desc">
            A wargame construction kit. Digitize the map with hexwright, build the order of
            battle with musterwright, keep the whole game in plain JSON files you own. These
            are the tools behind the commissioned modules on this site. Full page at
            <a href="/kit">/kit</a>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span
              ><span class="dot live"></span><span class="k">Status</span><span class="v"
                >Public</span
              ></span
            >
            <span><span class="k">License</span><span class="v">AGPL-3.0</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Access</span><span class="v">BYOK · local-first</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Ecosystem</span><span class="v">Mission apps</span></span>
          </div>
          <a href="/generalstaff" class="infra-title">GeneralStaff</a>
          <p class="infra-desc">
            Open-source autonomous engineering for solo founders. Verification-gated, BYOK,
            local-first. Repo at
            <a href="https://github.com/lerugray/generalstaff">github.com/lerugray/generalstaff</a>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span
              ><span class="dot live"></span><span class="k">Status</span><span class="v"
                >In daily use</span
              ></span
            >
            <span><span class="k">Surface</span><span class="v">CLI · slash command</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Cost</span><span class="v">~$0.01 per audit</span></span>
          </div>
          <a href="/hammerstein" class="infra-title">Hammerstein</a>
          <p class="infra-desc">
            Strategic-reasoning advisor tuned to the Hammerstein-Equord officer typology.
            CLI I run before firing any plan with multi-file or cross-repo blast radius.
            The framework essay it embodies is at
            <a href="/writing/hammerstein">Von Hammerstein's Ghost, In Daily Use</a>;
            repo at <a href="https://github.com/lerugray/hammerstein">github.com/lerugray/hammerstein</a>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="infra-meta">
            <span
              ><span class="dot live"></span><span class="k">Status</span><span class="v"
                >Public on HuggingFace</span
              ></span
            >
            <span><span class="k">Base</span><span class="v">Qwen2.5-7B-Instruct</span></span>
            <span><span class="k">Method</span><span class="v">QLoRA · rank 32</span></span>
          </div>
          <a href="/hammerstein-model" class="infra-title">Hammerstein-7B</a>
          <p class="infra-desc">
            A 7B QLoRA that bakes the strategic-reasoning framework into the weights of a
            small open base. Trained for $4 in a single day; runs on 8 GB Mac via
            <code>ollama run hf.co/lerugray/hammerstein-7b-lora:Q4_K_M</code>. Eval design
            and documented OOD boundary on the
            <a href="https://huggingface.co/lerugray/hammerstein-7b-lora">model card</a>.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="projects">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="projects">
          <span class="pl">PL. V</span>Projects
        </h2>
        <span class="section-count">04 entries ——</span>
      </div>
      <ol class="entries">
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>i.</em></div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="https://lerugray.github.io/the-elect/" class="entry-title">
              The Elect &rarr;
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              A roster of local voice models, each trained on the public-domain words of a
              historical figure to carry that register. Public-domain only, CC-BY-NC, disclaimed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>ii.</em></div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/auftragstaktik" class="entry-title">Auftragstaktik</a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              Tactical OSINT command terminal. Talked into shape in about two weeks via Claude
              Code.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>iii.</em></div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="/conflict-simulations-llc/veridian-contraption" class="entry-title">
              Veridian Contraption
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              An autonomous ASCII world-simulator of considerable density and dubious intent.
              Now playable in the browser.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <div class="index"><em>iv.</em></div>
          <div class="entry">
            <a href="https://lerugray.github.io/yoon-suin/" class="entry-title">
              Solo RPG campaigns &rarr;
            </a>
            <p class="entry-desc">
              A Whitehack × Yoon-Suin solo campaign vault. The Yellow City, played turn by turn.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="music-block" aria-labelledby="music">
      <div class="section-head">
        <h2 class="section-label" id="music">
          <span class="pl">PL. VI</span>Music
        </h2>
        <span class="section-count">01 entry ——</span>
      </div>
      <p>
        <a href="/music">Le Rug</a>,
        <span class="muted"
          >with Sweet Bulbs and Butter The Children before that. Brooklyn projects from a former
          life.</span
        >
      </p>
      <a href="/music" class="follow">Listen &rarr;</a>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
